25/06/2007
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Police arrested five people with suspected links to al-Qaeda, ahead of Monday's (June 25th) Black Sea summit in Istanbul. Russian President Vladimir Putin is attending the event and officials say Chechens were among those detained. Last week, security forces detained 23 alleged al-Qaeda members in the northwest province of Bursa, while a month ago, 11 others were apprehended in Istanbul. 
In other news, officials confirmed on Sunday that eight people were killed in weekend clashes between Turkish security forces and militants from the terrorist Kurdistan Workers Party. (Sabah, AFP - 25/06/07; AP, Reuters - 24/06/07)
